"meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Camille, Jacques, Armand, Marcel, Andre, Pierre, Serge, Yvan, Alphonse, Edouard, Francois, Gaetane.  Spanish Jose, Carlos, Jorge, Roberto, Angel, Francisco, Joaquin, Juan, Manuel, Miguel, Ramon, Rolando.","French, Walloon, Breton, West Indian (mainly Haiti), German, Dutch, English, and Portuguese; Spanish and Galician (<b>Denís</b>): from the personal name <i>Denis</i>, Spanish and Galician <i>Denís</i>, from Latin <i>Dionysius</i> ‘(follower) of Dionysos’ (see   Dennis  ). Compare   Dennee  .","Ukrainian and Rusyn: variant transliteration of   Denys  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Helena","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Portuguese: from the personal name <i>Helena</i>, from Latin <i>Helena</i>, of Greek origin, related to <i>helanē</i> ‘torch’ and <i>helē</i> ‘brightness of the sun’. The popularity of this as a personal name is due largely to Saint Helena, mother of the Emperor Constantine, who was influential as a Christian proselytizer in Byzantium."],"variants":[{"name":"Elenis","meanings":["(2010: NA)","Greek: metronymic from the female personal name <i>Eleni</i> (classical Greek <i>Helenē</i>) ‘Helen’; see   Helena  ."]},{"name":"Elena","meanings":["Spanish and Italian: from the female personal name <i>Elena</i>, from Latin   Helena  , of Greek origin."]}]},{"name":"Beatrice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and French form of   Beatrix  , which was quite popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":18,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrice de St Helena was born about 1272, in Crowell, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, John St. Elena, was 25 and her mother, Juliana Farnham, was 24. She married Giles de Braose about 1288. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 1 June 1298, in Knowlton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 27, and was buried in Horton, Dorset, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1272–1 June 1298":"umbes 1272–1. juuni 1298","1272–1298":"1272–1298","1268–1305":"1268–1305","1293–Female":"1293–Surnud","1248–1295":"1248–1295","1250–1295":"1250–1295","about 1272":"umbes 1272","1 June 1298":"1. juuni 1298","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1248":"1248","1268":"1268","17 May 1293":"17. mai 1293","1298":"1298","about 1288":"umbes 1288","before 21 July 1295":"enne 21. juulit 1295","AFT 1295":"pärast 1295","Crowell,Oxfordshire,England":"Crowell, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Horton, East Dorset District, Dorset, England":"Horton, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Crowell, Oxfordshire, England":"Crowell, Oxfordshire, England","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England","Knowlton, Dorset, England":"Knowlton, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1272–1 June 1298":"noin 1272–1. kesäkuuta 1298","1272–1298":"1272–1298","1268–1305":"1268–1305","1293–Female":"1293–Kuollut","1248–1295":"1248–1295","1250–1295":"1250–1295","about 1272":"noin 1272","1 June 1298":"1. kesäkuuta 1298","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1248":"1248","1268":"1268","17 May 1293":"17. toukokuuta 1293","1298":"1298","about 1288":"noin 1288","before 21 July 1295":"ennen vuotta 21. heinäkuuta 1295","AFT 1295":"1295 jälkeen","Crowell,Oxfordshire,England":"Crowell, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Horton, East Dorset 